Configuration of the mapping amongst the font families used in the user application (e.g. Arial) and the physical files actually used during spool phase generation (e.g. *arial.ttf, arialb.ttf *etc.).

## Accessing the font settings
The **Font **tab allows to access and configure the font settings.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Adding a Family
- Click **Add family **to create a Family.

- Enter the identifier of the Family in the **New font family **window.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Click **New **or press **Enter **to confirm the creation and close the window. The Family which has just been created will be selected.

> Warning

The Create font family window validates the value entered for the identifier. If the field is empty or the value used is the same as another Family identifier, creation is not possible. 

## Deleting a Family
- Click the name of a Family to select it.

- Click **Delete family**.

> Warning

No confirmation is requested before deletion of a Family.

## Modifying the name of a Family
- Click the name of a Family to select it.

- In the Family's properties, click **Change... **next to the name.

- Enter the new name of the Family in the **Edit font family **window.

- Click **Apply **or press **Enter **to confirm the modification and close the window.

> Warning

The Edit font family window validates the value entered for the name. If the field is empty or the value used is the same as another Family name, modification is not possible.

## Setting the CSS font family
Font family to be used in the HTML emitter.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

# 
## Embedding fonts and changing their names
The panel containing the properties of a Family shows the configuration for each font style associated to it.

- For each style, select **enable **to allow the production of text with that style for that Family.  

- For each style, enter the physical filename in the **File name **text field.

- For each style, select the checkboxes that correspond to the characters code pages you want to enable  

- For each style, select **embed **to force embedding of the font file in the documents produced.

- Click **Enable all **to enable all the styles.  

- Click **Disable all **to disable all the styles. 

- Click **Embed all **to embed the font file of all the styles.

- Click **Embed none **to embed none of the style font files.
